                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1833: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-09-24T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. Your 252, September 22, 9 a.m. No new proposals for Nicaraguan financing
                    have been brought to the Department’s attention since you were in Washington.
                    You will be kept informed by telegraph of any important developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
